ope for which little is known\nyet. An important conclusion is that the infrared spectra of K - M giants are a\nhybrid of at least two components originating in the photosphere and the warm\nmolecular envelope. In the interpretation and analysis of the infrared spectra\nof cool luminous stars, it is essential to keep their hybrid naure in mind.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Jul 2008 09:22:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 Oct 2008 11:37:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
